-- Aramco Names Al-Dabbagh Treasurer, Al-Ma'ashouq VP of Business Development
-- B y   V i v i a n   S a l a m a
-- 2010-11-06T15:57:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-06/aramco-names-al-dabbagh-treasurer-al-ma-ashouq-vp-of-business-development.html
Saudi Aramco, the world’s largest oil
producer, said  Motassim A. Al-Ma ‘ashouq was appointed vice
president of new business development, and  Khalid H. Al-Dabbagh 
was named treasurer.  Al-Ma’ashouq previously served as president and chief
executive officer of Saudi Arabian Lubricating Oil Co. in
Jeddah, according to a statement today on Saudi Aramco’s
 website . He also served as vice president of corporate planning
at Petron Corp., Saudi Aramco’s affiliate in the Philippines,
and chairman for the Philippines Institute of Petroleum.  Al-Dabbagh previously worked as president and CEO of Saudi
Petroleum International Inc. He has also served as board
director of Showa Shell, Fujian Refining and Petrochemical Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Vivian Salama  in Kuwait through the Abu Dhabi newsroom at   vsalama@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter Hirschberg at 
 phirschberg@bloomberg.net . 